We went here for the R&B bottomless mimosa brunch. I must say that it was not what I was expecting. It was pretty empty and there was good R&B playing in the background. The bottomless mimosas were $18 per person which is not too bad. The problem that I had was the lackluster menu. There is not much variety and I ended up getting the steak and eggs. The steak was poorly seasoned and very thin. They did not have any type of steak sauce and they did not have many veggie options or salad dressings. It is a nice little place with a good atmosphere but they definitely have to do 90% better with their menu. With that being said, I probably would not opt to return because of the menu. I can't attest for the drinks besides the mimosas and those were decent.

My first time at Library Tavern was a Friday evening for a friend's birthday.  We were a bigger group of about 10-12 (maybe 15) people.  We sat outside in the patio area. Good food, great hookah, and the staff was very accommodating.  A week later (9/7/19) I had to plan a going away party for a friend.  Luckily, I was able to book the downstairs lounge.  AMAZING, AMAZING, AMAZING!!  The manager made us all feel right at home.  We were able to decorate, control the music, and just hang out in our very own private space.  Everyone was beyond happy with the venue, the customer service, and the food!  They even let us stay past closing time and in no way made us feel rushed to leave.  I strongly recommend this place for dinner, happy hour on the patio, and definitely a very TOP venue option if you have to throw a party or other type of social event.  The downstairs lounge is cozy, intimate, and just the perfect set up to accommodate many needs.  THANK YOU to management at Library Tavern for making the special going away party such a great success!!!  As a local in the area, I have no doubts I will be back!!

Ate here with my lady on Saturday.  At first was impressed with venue and atmosphere.  Soon after noticed some customer service issues that need to be addressed.  We waited almost an hour for our food before we made a formal complaint to the bartender.  He stated there were only two cooks available.  However the issue that took us over the top was people who arrived after us got their food first even after the complaint.  Apparently they didn't get our order and others as well. If you acknowledge a customer service issue you remedy it ASAP... Not sure if I will try again as the bartender was dope but he isn't a manager.
